[normal]Domestic violence is defined as “any incident of threatening behaviour, violence or abuse (psychological, physical, sexual, financial, emotional) between adults who are or 
[normal]have been intimate partners or family members regardless of gender or sexuality”. The minimum has recently been lowered from 18 to 16.
